                       Collegelo em nerchukunnaru SPARK: A View is a virtual table created from a SQL query

View does not store data physically (unless its a materialized view in other systems)
Instead, it stores the query definition

When you query the view, MySQL runs the underlying query
=> A view is a saved SQL query that behaves like a table antee chudham

A view in MySQL is a virtual and temporary table defined by a stored SQL query
-- It doesn’t store data physically but retrieves data dynamically from underlying tables when queried. Views act like shortcuts to complex queries, providing a simplified interface for users or applications to work with particular data by taking access.
=> It is a temporary purpose means once we close MySQL Workbench window the created View tables won't be visible 

CREATE VIEW high_rent_properties AS
SELECT property_id, locality, rent
FROM properties
WHERE rent > 50000;

SELECT * FROM high_rent_properties;

